## ğŸ”„ Traversal Rules

Traversal rules define relationships between CIs during tag-based service mapping.

### ğŸ“Œ Usage:
- Used in **tag-based mapping** to build service maps.
- Define parent-child relationships (e.g., Linux Server â†’ Storage Device).
- Configured in the **Traversal Rules for Application Services** form.

ğŸ”— [Traversal Rules Documentation](https://www.servicenow.com/docs/bundle/washingtondc-it-operations-management/page/product/service-mapping/reference/traversal_rules_form_completion.html)

